18/08/2009
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Train drivers in the Federation of Bosnia and Herzegovina (FBiH) announced on Monday (August 17th) plans to go on strike on August 28th. 
Trains in all major cities -- Sarajevo, Zenica, Mostar, Tuzla and Bihac -- will stop at 7am. 
Trade unions insist the government should drop plans to cut salaries in the sector by 10%. 
The drivers also demand back wages owed them. 
(Fena, Sarajevo-x.com - 17/08/09)
